67
00:03:31,220 --> 00:03:33,150
♪

68
00:03:38,490 --> 00:03:40,160
( Eugeo gasping )

69
00:03:43,430 --> 00:03:44,430
( Kirito gasps ) Euge--

70
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:46,330
- ( blade stabs )
- ( Groaning )

71
00:03:49,340 --> 00:03:53,840
( Fizel chuckles ) My name
is fizel synthesis twenty-nine.

72
00:03:53,910 --> 00:03:56,280
Eugeo: You’re a...

73
00:03:57,610 --> 00:03:59,550
Integri...

74
00:03:59,610 --> 00:04:01,420
( Both groan )

75
00:04:06,620 --> 00:04:09,520
linel: Don’t fret,
eugeo without-a-last-name.

76
00:04:09,590 --> 00:04:11,390
You’re ours now.

77
00:04:12,830 --> 00:04:14,760
( Footsteps shuffling )

78
00:04:16,970 --> 00:04:17,970
( Eugeo grunting )

79
00:04:18,030 --> 00:04:19,870
Linel: It’s a paralysis poison.

80
00:04:19,930 --> 00:04:22,470
We don’t want you to die yet,

81
00:04:22,540 --> 00:04:25,440
not until we get you
to the 50th floor, anyway.

82
00:04:25,510 --> 00:04:27,880
i’m sure
you must be wondering...

83
00:04:28,940 --> 00:04:30,480
"How in the world

84
00:04:30,550 --> 00:04:32,910
did these two little girls
become integrity knights?"

85
00:04:32,980 --> 00:04:34,850
( Eugeo gasping )

86
00:04:36,650 --> 00:04:39,820
Linel: We were born and raised
inside the central cathedral.

87
00:04:40,890 --> 00:04:43,660
One day, administrator herself

88
00:04:43,730 --> 00:04:46,430
ordered the monks and nuns here
to create us.

89
00:04:47,630 --> 00:04:49,230
She needed test subjects

90
00:04:49,300 --> 00:04:51,770
for a sacred art
she was experimenting with

91
00:04:51,830 --> 00:04:53,840
that could resurrect the dead.

92
00:04:55,340 --> 00:04:58,310
We received our callings
when we were five,

93
00:04:58,370 --> 00:04:59,840
earlier than other children.

94
00:04:59,910 --> 00:05:03,650
Our job was to kill each other.

95
00:05:03,710 --> 00:05:06,550
We were given little swords
that looked like toys.

96
00:05:06,610 --> 00:05:09,920
then, we’d pair off and
take turns stabbing each other.

97
00:05:09,980 --> 00:05:11,920
( Singers vocalizing )

98
00:05:11,990 --> 00:05:13,920
♪

99
00:05:19,430 --> 00:05:20,530
( Blade stabs )

100
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:45,290
Fizel: At first, administrator’s
attempts at resurrection were--

101
00:05:45,350 --> 00:05:47,560
how shall I say? Not so good.

102
00:05:48,790 --> 00:05:51,360
There were some children
who exploded

103
00:05:51,430 --> 00:05:55,630
and others who ended up
as weird blobs of flesh.

104
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:59,330
And still others who returned,
but were different.

105
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,940
Linel: We were being
resurrected over and over,

106
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,310
but we didn’t like
dying in pain,

107
00:06:04,370 --> 00:06:07,480
so the two of us researched
how to kill with one strike.

108
00:06:07,540 --> 00:06:09,340
We found that if
we killed cleanly,

109
00:06:09,410 --> 00:06:11,810
it didn’t hurt as much
and the odds of being

110
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:14,880
successfully resurrected
were higher,

111
00:06:14,950 --> 00:06:16,680
but...

112
00:06:16,750 --> 00:06:20,690
The problem was deciding
which strike worked the best.

113
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:23,660
We narrowed it down
to lopping off the head

114
00:06:23,730 --> 00:06:27,630
or a quick stab to the heart.
They both worked equally well.

115
00:06:30,270 --> 00:06:31,430
In the end, though,

116
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:33,530
administrator decided
it was too difficult

117
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,940
to master the sacred art
of resurrection.

118
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,610
We were about eight years old

119
00:06:37,670 --> 00:06:40,540
when she abandoned
the experiment.

120
00:06:40,610 --> 00:06:43,240
When it started,
there were 30 of us,

121
00:06:43,310 --> 00:06:45,650
but zel and I
were the only survivors.

122
00:06:45,710 --> 00:06:47,650
( Eugeo gasping )

123
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:52,750
Linel: Then administrator
made a special exception

124
00:06:52,820 --> 00:06:54,790
and made us integrity knights.

125
00:06:54,860 --> 00:06:56,890
Well, to a certain degree.

126
00:06:56,960 --> 00:06:58,760
she said
we hadn’t learned enough

127
00:06:58,830 --> 00:07:01,460
to go on guard duty
like the other knights,

128
00:07:01,530 --> 00:07:04,230
so we’ve been studying
the laws and sacred arts

129
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:06,940
with the other apprentices
for the past two years.

130
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,870
To be honest,
we’re tired of it.

131
00:07:11,470 --> 00:07:13,710
Fizel: Earlier today,
we were discussing ways

132
00:07:13,780 --> 00:07:17,210
to earn our dragons
and divine objects more quickly.

133
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:19,580
We heard that minions
from the dark territory

134
00:07:19,650 --> 00:07:22,250
had infiltrated the cathedral,

135
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:25,190
so we thought, if we could
capture and execute them

136
00:07:25,250 --> 00:07:26,790
before the other knights could,

137
00:07:26,850 --> 00:07:29,520
it would show administrator
how capable we were

138
00:07:29,590 --> 00:07:31,530
and she would make us
full-fledged knights,

139
00:07:31,590 --> 00:07:33,400
so we waited on the stairs.

140
00:07:35,860 --> 00:07:38,630
Linel: We’re truly sorry
for using poison on you.

141
00:07:38,700 --> 00:07:40,970
It was our only option.

142
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:43,200
you see,
we wanted to bring you

143
00:07:43,270 --> 00:07:45,410
to the 50th floor alive,
if possible.

144
00:07:45,470 --> 00:07:48,840
Oh, and when we do get there,
don’t you worry.

145
00:07:48,910 --> 00:07:51,580
fizel and I
are really good at killing.

146
00:07:51,650 --> 00:07:53,280
It won’t hurt at all.

147
00:07:59,790 --> 00:08:02,620
( Both groan )

148
00:08:02,690 --> 00:08:04,630
♪

149
00:08:09,230 --> 00:08:13,530
Linel: Well, well, if it isn’t
all four of the whirling blades,

150
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:17,770
as well as vice commander
fanatio synthesis two.

151
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:20,280
Fizel: The whole senate
must be in a panic.

152
00:08:20,340 --> 00:08:22,180
why else
would they ask you here,

153
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:24,380
fanatio of
the heaven-piercing blade?

154
00:08:24,450 --> 00:08:28,380
fanatio: You apprentices
should not be on the battlefield

155
00:08:28,450 --> 00:08:29,750
with honorable knights.

156
00:08:29,820 --> 00:08:32,520
( Fizel laughs )
Now, that is funny!

157
00:08:32,590 --> 00:08:35,620
It’s because you bring honor
and tradition into battle,

158
00:08:35,690 --> 00:08:38,390
that you so-called
mighty integrity knights lost

159
00:08:38,460 --> 00:08:40,800
not once, but twice!

160
00:08:40,860 --> 00:08:42,460
But don’t you worry.

161
00:08:42,530 --> 00:08:44,770
as you can see,
we caught the intruders,

162
00:08:44,830 --> 00:08:47,400
and we’ll make sure
the reputation of the knights

163
00:08:47,470 --> 00:08:50,740
won’t be sullied any further.
You can count on that.

164
00:08:50,810 --> 00:08:52,210
Linel: She’s right!

165
00:08:52,270 --> 00:08:53,740
We’re going to decapitate
these sinners

166
00:08:53,810 --> 00:08:54,940
right here and now,

167
00:08:55,010 --> 00:08:57,310
so watch closely, and make sure

168
00:08:57,380 --> 00:09:00,480
to give an accurate report
to the pontifex.

169
00:09:00,550 --> 00:09:02,880
You are honorable knights,
after all.

170
00:09:02,950 --> 00:09:05,390
we trust you
not to steal our credit.

171
00:09:05,450 --> 00:09:06,850
That would be cowardly.

172
00:09:06,920 --> 00:09:08,790
♪

173
00:09:12,330 --> 00:09:13,600
( Girls gasp )

174
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:16,660
Linel: No fair.

175
00:09:16,730 --> 00:09:18,330
Fizel: I can’t...

176
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:19,470
( Both moan )

177
00:09:27,910 --> 00:09:29,840
( Linel shuddering )

178
00:09:38,520 --> 00:09:39,650
( Eugeo groans )

179
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:41,360
Kirito: It’ll wear off
in a minute.

180
00:09:41,420 --> 00:09:44,590
As soon as you can move
your lips again,

181
00:09:44,660 --> 00:09:47,500
recite your perfect weapon art,
but keep it down.

182
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:49,600
This ain’t gonna work
if the knights hear.

183
00:09:49,660 --> 00:09:50,900
When it’s ready to go,

184
00:09:50,970 --> 00:09:52,570
hang on to it a bit.

185
00:09:52,630 --> 00:09:54,340
Wait for my signal.

186
00:09:59,870 --> 00:10:03,280
I’m sure you’re wondering,
how in the world can I move?

187
00:10:05,450 --> 00:10:08,250
You gave yourselves away.

188
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:10,850
You said all the monks,
nuns, and apprentices

189
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:13,090
were ordered
to stay in their rooms,

190
00:10:13,150 --> 00:10:15,420
and if you’re a monk,
nun, or apprentice,

191
00:10:15,490 --> 00:10:18,130
there’s no way you’d
disobey the church’s order.

192
00:10:19,260 --> 00:10:20,430
But you weren’t in your rooms.

193
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:22,030
You were looking for us,

194
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:24,400
so that meant you guys
weren’t real apprentices.

195
00:10:26,870 --> 00:10:30,070
I also noticed those scabbards
you got are made of Ruby oak.

196
00:10:30,140 --> 00:10:31,310
They use that wood

197
00:10:31,370 --> 00:10:34,140
to hold swords
made of toxic ruberyl steel.

198
00:10:34,210 --> 00:10:36,140
Why? ’cause it’s the only thing

199
00:10:36,210 --> 00:10:38,350
that won’t rot
against the blade.

200
00:10:38,410 --> 00:10:40,250
there’s no way
you’d have something like that

201
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:41,980
if you were sisters-in-training.

202
00:10:42,050 --> 00:10:46,020
That’s why I started reciting
a poison-neutralizing art

203
00:10:46,090 --> 00:10:47,760
before you got near us.

204
00:10:47,820 --> 00:10:51,930
It took a while to kick in,
but what can you do?

205
00:10:51,990 --> 00:10:55,300
There’s more to strength
than bein’ fast with a sword.

206
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:58,470
( Fizel gasping )

207
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:03,070
( Blades slice )

208
00:11:05,770 --> 00:11:07,680
( Both sigh )

209
00:11:07,740 --> 00:11:09,980
Don’t worry. I won’t kill you.

210
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:12,750
I’m gonna teach you
a lesson today.

211
00:11:12,810 --> 00:11:15,320
You’re gonna watch these knights
you made fun of fight

212
00:11:15,380 --> 00:11:17,290
and see what real strength’s
all about.

213
00:11:17,350 --> 00:11:19,450
( Footsteps receding )

214
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:21,460
♪

215
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:30,400
Sorry for the wait,
vice commander fanatio.

216
00:11:35,070 --> 00:11:38,340
My name’s kirito,
the swordsman!

217
00:11:43,780 --> 00:11:45,710
♪

218
00:11:50,790 --> 00:11:51,820
( Yells )

219
00:11:57,460 --> 00:12:00,830
Woman: How dare you do battle
with the vice commander?!

220
00:12:00,900 --> 00:12:03,700
The four whirling blades
are your opponents here!

221
00:12:03,770 --> 00:12:05,100
Turn and face us!

222
00:12:05,170 --> 00:12:07,070
Fanatio: Hold your position.

223
00:12:07,140 --> 00:12:10,710
This one is mine.

224
00:12:10,770 --> 00:12:11,970
Woman: As you wish.

225
00:12:18,380 --> 00:12:20,350
Fanatio: System call.

226
00:12:20,420 --> 00:12:22,980
Enhance armament!

227
00:12:25,250 --> 00:12:27,920
( Kirito growls )

228
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:31,790
( Yells )

229
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:36,130
( Groans )

230
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:37,130
( Yells )

231
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:41,870
( Sighs )

232
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:46,410
( Gasps )

233
00:12:58,850 --> 00:12:59,790
( Gasps )

234
00:13:03,190 --> 00:13:04,260
Eugeo: Ki--

235
00:13:04,330 --> 00:13:05,730
( gasps )

236
00:13:05,790 --> 00:13:07,800
My voice.

237
00:13:07,860 --> 00:13:08,860
It’s back!

238
00:13:09,930 --> 00:13:11,700
System call.

239
00:13:11,770 --> 00:13:13,700
( Kirito groaning )

240
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:23,880
Fanatio: Criminal or no,
if you lived in centoria,

241
00:13:23,950 --> 00:13:26,110
you should know
what a mirror is.

242
00:13:28,820 --> 00:13:30,180
It is an instrument

243
00:13:30,250 --> 00:13:34,290
capable of reflecting
solus’s light completely.

244
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:39,290
Long ago, the pontifex gathered
1,000 enormous mirrors

245
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:41,900
to focus solus’s
midsummer light,

246
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:44,270
creating a pure, white flame.

247
00:13:44,330 --> 00:13:46,370
It was so hot,

248
00:13:46,430 --> 00:13:50,270
